section.section:
In determining whether or not to seek assessment of a civil penalty, the Department shall consider:
The willfullness of the violation and whether any negligence was involved;
The seriousness of the violation in terms of potential or actual damage to land and structures, irreparable harm to the environment, or hazard to the health or safety of the public;
The history of violations at the particular mine site;
Any demonstrated good faith by the operator in attempting rapid compliance after notification of the violation; and
The effect of the violation on reclamation of the affected area.

text.section:
The Department may waive assessment of the civil penalty required by subsection (c) of this section when a violation was issued for the failure of the operator to submit:
The monthly report and annual report required under § 15-508(a) of this subtitle;
The mining and reclamation progress report required under § 15-508(b) of this subtitle;
The backfilling and planting report required under § 15-513 of this subtitle; or
The completion report required under § 15-511(a) of this subtitle.
